{"type":"USJ","version":"3.1","content":[{"type":"book","marker":"id","content":["61-2PE-web.sfm English Arabic Names Version (EANV)"],"code":"2PE"},{"type":"para","marker":"ide","content":["UTF-8\n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"h","content":["2 Peter \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"toc1","content":["Peter’s Second Letter \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"toc2","content":["2 Peter \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"toc3","content":["2Pe \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"mt1","content":["Peter’s Second Letter \n"]},{"type":"chapter","marker":"c","number":"1","sid":"2PE 1"},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"1","sid":"2PE 1:1"},"Shima’un Peter, a servant and apostle of Al Masih Isa, to those who have obtained a like precious faith with us in the\nrighteousness of our Allah and Saviour, Al Masih Isa: \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"2","sid":"2PE 1:2"},"Grace to you and peace be multiplied in the knowledge of Allah and of Isa our Lord,\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"3","sid":"2PE 1:3"},"seeing that his divine power has granted to us all things that pertain to life and godliness, through the knowledge of him\nwho called us by his own glory and virtue, \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"4","sid":"2PE 1:4"},"by which he has granted to us his precious and exceedingly great promises; that through these you may become partakers of\nthe divine nature, having escaped from the corruption that is in the world by lust.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"5","sid":"2PE 1:5"},"Yes, and for this very cause adding on your part all diligence, in your faith supply moral excellence; and in moral\nexcellence, knowledge; \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"6","sid":"2PE 1:6"},"and in knowledge, self-control; and in self-control perseverance; and in perseverance godliness;\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"7","sid":"2PE 1:7"},"and in godliness brotherly affection; and in brotherly affection, love.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"8","sid":"2PE 1:8"},"For if these things are yours and abound, they make you to not be idle or unfruitful in the knowledge of our Lord Al Masih\nIsa. \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"9","sid":"2PE 1:9"},"For he who lacks these things is blind, seeing only what is near, having forgotten the cleansing from his old sins.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"10","sid":"2PE 1:10"},"Therefore, brothers,",{"type":"note","marker":"f","content":["  ",{"type":"char","marker":"fr","content":["1:10 "]},{"type":"char","marker":"ft","content":["The word for “brothers” here and where context allows may also be correctly\ntranslated “brothers and sisters” or “siblings.” "]}],"caller":"+"}," be more diligent to make your calling and election sure. For if you do\nthese things, you will never stumble. \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"11","sid":"2PE 1:11"},"For thus you will be richly supplied with the entrance into the eternal Kingdom of our Lord and Saviour, Al Masih Isa.\n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"12","sid":"2PE 1:12"},"Therefore I will not be negligent to remind you of these things, though you know them, and are established in the present\ntruth. \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"13","sid":"2PE 1:13"},"I think it right, as long as I am in this tent, to stir you up by reminding you,\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"14","sid":"2PE 1:14"},"knowing that the putting off of my tent comes swiftly, even as our Lord Al Masih Isa made clear to me.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"15","sid":"2PE 1:15"},"Yes, I will make every effort that you may always be able to remember these things even after my departure.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"16","sid":"2PE 1:16"},"For we didn’t follow cunningly devised fables when we made known to you the power and coming of our Lord Al Masih Isa,\nbut we were eyewitnesses of his majesty. \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"17","sid":"2PE 1:17"},"For he received from Allah the Father honour and glory when the voice came to him from the Majestic Glory, “This is my\nbeloved Son, in whom I am well pleased.”",{"type":"note","marker":"x","content":[{"type":"char","marker":"xo","content":["1:17 "]},{"type":"char","marker":"xt","content":["Matti\n17:5; Marqus 9:7; Luqa 9:35"]}],"caller":"+"}," \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"18","sid":"2PE 1:18"},"We heard this voice come out of heaven when we were with him on the holy mountain.\n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"19","sid":"2PE 1:19"},"We have the more sure word of prophecy; and you do well that you heed it, as to a lamp shining in a dark place, until the\nday dawns, and the morning star arises in your hearts: \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"20","sid":"2PE 1:20"},"knowing this first, that no prophecy of Scripture is of private interpretation.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"21","sid":"2PE 1:21"},"For no prophecy ever came by the will of man: but holy men of Allah spoke, being moved by the Holy Spirit.\n"]},{"type":"chapter","marker":"c","number":"2","sid":"2PE 2"},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"1","sid":"2PE 2:1"},"But false prophets also arose amongst the people, as false teachers will also be amongst you, who will secretly bring in\ndestructive heresies, denying even the Master who bought them, bringing on themselves swift destruction.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"2","sid":"2PE 2:2"},"Many will follow their immoral",{"type":"note","marker":"f","content":["  ",{"type":"char","marker":"fr","content":["2:2 "]},{"type":"char","marker":"ft","content":["TR reads “destructive” instead of\n“immoral”"]}],"caller":"+"}," ways, and as a result, the way of the truth will be maligned.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"3","sid":"2PE 2:3"},"In covetousness they will exploit you with deceptive words: whose sentence now from of old doesn’t linger, and their\ndestruction will not slumber. \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"4","sid":"2PE 2:4"},"For if Allah didn’t spare angels when they sinned, but cast them down to\nTartarus,",{"type":"note","marker":"f","content":["  ",{"type":"char","marker":"fr","content":["2:4 "]},{"type":"char","marker":"ft","content":["Tartarus is another name for Hell"]}],"caller":"+"}," and committed them to pits of darkness to be reserved for\njudgement; \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"5","sid":"2PE 2:5"},"and didn’t spare the ancient world, but preserved Nuh with seven others, a preacher of righteousness, when he brought a\nflood on the world of the ungodly; \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"6","sid":"2PE 2:6"},"and turning the cities of Sodom and Gomorrah into ashes, condemned them to destruction, having made them an example to\nthose who would live in an ungodly way; \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"7","sid":"2PE 2:7"},"and delivered righteous Lut, who was very distressed by the lustful life of the wicked\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"8","sid":"2PE 2:8"},"(for that righteous man dwelling amongst them was tormented in his righteous soul from day to day with seeing and hearing\nlawless deeds): \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"9","sid":"2PE 2:9"},"the Lord knows how to deliver the godly out of temptation and to keep the unrighteous under punishment for the day of\njudgement, \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"10","sid":"2PE 2:10"},"but chiefly those who walk after the flesh in the lust of defilement and despise authority. Daring, self-willed, they are\nnot afraid to speak evil of dignitaries; \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"11","sid":"2PE 2:11"},"whereas angels, though greater in might and power, don’t bring a railing judgement against them before the Lord.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"12","sid":"2PE 2:12"},"But these, as unreasoning creatures, born natural animals to be taken and destroyed, speaking evil in matters about which\nthey are ignorant, will in their destroying surely be destroyed,\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"13","sid":"2PE 2:13"},"receiving the wages of unrighteousness; people who count it pleasure to revel in the daytime, spots and defects,\nrevelling in their deceit while they feast with you; \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"14","sid":"2PE 2:14"},"having eyes full of adultery, and who can’t cease from sin; enticing unsettled souls; having a heart trained in greed;\nchildren of cursing; \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"15","sid":"2PE 2:15"},"forsaking the right way, they went astray, having followed the way of Balaam the son of Beor, who loved the wages of\nwrongdoing; \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"16","sid":"2PE 2:16"},"but he was rebuked for his own disobedience. A mute donkey spoke with a man’s voice and stopped the madness of the\nprophet. \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"17","sid":"2PE 2:17"},"These are wells without water, clouds driven by a storm; for whom the blackness of darkness has been reserved forever.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"18","sid":"2PE 2:18"},"For, uttering great swelling words of emptiness, they entice in the lusts of the flesh, by licentiousness, those who are\nindeed escaping from those who live in error; \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"19","sid":"2PE 2:19"},"promising them liberty, while they themselves are bondservants of corruption; for a man is brought into bondage by\nwhoever overcomes him. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"20","sid":"2PE 2:20"},"For if, after they have escaped the defilement of the world through the knowledge of the Lord and Saviour Al Masih Isa,\nthey are again entangled in it and overcome, the last state has become worse for them than the first.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"21","sid":"2PE 2:21"},"For it would be better for them not to have known the way of righteousness, than after knowing it, to turn back from the\nholy commandment delivered to them. \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"22","sid":"2PE 2:22"},"But it has happened to them according to the true proverb, “The dog turns to his own vomit\nagain,”",{"type":"note","marker":"x","content":[{"type":"char","marker":"xo","content":["2:22 "]},{"type":"char","marker":"xt","content":["Proverbs 26:11"]}],"caller":"+"}," and “the sow that has washed to wallowing in the mire.”\n"]},{"type":"chapter","marker":"c","number":"3","sid":"2PE 3"},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"1","sid":"2PE 3:1"},"This is now, beloved, the second letter that I have written to you; and in both of them I stir up your sincere mind by\nreminding you, \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"2","sid":"2PE 3:2"},"that you should remember the words which were spoken before by the holy prophets, and the commandment of us, the apostles\nof the Lord and Saviour: \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"3","sid":"2PE 3:3"},"knowing this first, that in the last days mockers will come, walking after their own lusts\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"4","sid":"2PE 3:4"},"and saying, “Where is the promise of his coming? For, from the day that the fathers fell asleep, all things continue as\nthey were from the beginning of the creation.” \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"5","sid":"2PE 3:5"},"For this they wilfully forget that there were heavens from of old, and an earth formed out of water and amid water by the\nword of Allah, \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"6","sid":"2PE 3:6"},"by which means the world that existed then, being overflowed with water, perished.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"7","sid":"2PE 3:7"},"But the heavens that exist now and the earth, by the same word have been stored up for fire, being reserved against the\nday of judgement and destruction of ungodly men. \n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"8","sid":"2PE 3:8"},"But don’t forget this one thing, beloved, that one day is with the Lord as a thousand years, and a thousand years as one\nday. \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"9","sid":"2PE 3:9"},"The Lord is not slow concerning his promise, as some count slowness; but he is patient with us, not wishing that anyone\nshould perish, but that all should come to repentance. \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"10","sid":"2PE 3:10"},"But the day of the Lord will come as a thief in the night; in which the heavens will pass away with a great noise, and\nthe elements will be dissolved with fervent heat, and the earth and the works that are in it will be burnt up.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"11","sid":"2PE 3:11"},"Therefore since all these things will be destroyed like this, what kind of people ought you to be in holy living and\ngodliness, \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"12","sid":"2PE 3:12"},"looking for and earnestly desiring the coming of the day of Allah, which will cause the burning heavens to be dissolved,\nand the elements will melt with fervent heat? \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"13","sid":"2PE 3:13"},"But, according to his promise, we look for new heavens and a new earth, in which righteousness dwells.\n"]},{"type":"para","marker":"p","content":[{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"14","sid":"2PE 3:14"},"Therefore, beloved, seeing that you look for these things, be diligent to be found in peace, without defect and blameless\nin his sight. \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"15","sid":"2PE 3:15"},"Regard the patience of our Lord as salvation; even as our beloved brother Paul also, according to the wisdom given to\nhim, wrote to you, \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"16","sid":"2PE 3:16"},"as also in all of his letters, speaking in them of these things. In those, there are some things that are hard to\nunderstand, which the ignorant and unsettled twist, as they also do to the other Scriptures, to their own destruction.\n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"17","sid":"2PE 3:17"},"You therefore, beloved, knowing these things beforehand, beware, lest being carried away with the error of the wicked,\nyou fall from your own steadfastness. \n",{"type":"verse","marker":"v","number":"18","sid":"2PE 3:18"},"But grow in the grace and knowledge of our Lord and Saviour Al Masih Isa. To him be the glory both now and forever. Amen.\n"]}]}